│ when I try to fix it.                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The key is to ensure that the inner comparison, `XeqY`, is *exactly* `icmp eq i64 %X, %Y`, where `X` and `Y` are the values bound from the outer comparisons. The existing               │
│ `m_c_SpecificICmp` matcher is failing to enforce this correctly, leading to the miscompilations.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
